children.text: The stairs in this area have not been constructed with a landing to comply with the BCA.
Part 3.9.1.5 Landings of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) requires that
be not less than 750 mm long and where this involves a change in direction, the length is measured 500 mm from the inside edge of the landing (see Figure 3.9.1.3a);
have a gradient not steeper than 1:50;

be provided where the sill of a threshold of a doorway opens onto a stairway or ramp that provides a change in floor level or floor to ground level greater than 3 risers or 570 mm (see Figure 3.9.1.3b);
extend across the full width of a doorway;
in the case of a stairway serving only non-habitable rooms, such as attics, storerooms and the like that are not used
on a regular or daily basis, the requirements of (a) may be substituted with a minimum length of landing being not less than 600 mm long’ ;
A landing must be installed so that these stairs meet the requirements of the BCA.
